{
  "texts": [
    "AliDrone [61] is tailored to ensure that drones remain on drone lanes during their delivery runes.",
    "It uses trusted hardware to securely store proofs-of-alibi (GPS coordinates of the flight path) that can be used to prove to host airspaces that the drone was in compliance.",
    "PROTC [60] also uses trusted hardware on drones with a focus on protecting the drone software stack and peripherals from malicious attacks and rootkits [60].Ding et al. [41] consider how location broadcast systems like Remote ID can potentially compromise citizen privacy.",
    "They consider attacks whereby an attacker observing the drone's location can correlate drone trajectories with ground-based citizens and their purchases.",
    "They also develop methods to quantify privacy risks and generate routes that offer privacy."
  ]
}